<item>
 <title>Seriously Scalable Architecture With AWS</title>
 <link>http://2016.nerdsummit.org/nerdsummit-2014/sessions/seriously-scalable-architecture-aws</link>
 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Amazon Web Services&lt;/strong&gt; provides one of the most awesomely complicated suites of tools you can use to power a web application, which is why most of its users use less than 1% of its features. The primary goal of this session is to show you how companies like Netflix and Airbnb build bulletproof technology empires in the cloud using Amazon&#039;s IaaS.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Topics covered will include:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Custom private network topology&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Load balancing, monitoring, and autoscaling&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Cache clusters and queues&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Highly available relational databases&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Cloud storage and content delivery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This session is intended as a primer for building secure, scalable web infrastructure at low cost to you and your clients.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-experience field-type-list-text field-label-inline clearfix&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-label&quot;&gt;Experience level:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;Advanced&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-session-timeslot field-type-entityreference field-label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-label&quot;&gt;Session Time Slot(s):&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;entity entity-field-collection-item field-collection-item-field-event-timeslots clearfix&quot;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;content&quot;&gt;
